    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There already is a `Scatter` method, and it's doing exactly what you describe (even the forcing bit).\n\nThe only instance where it would fail if there aren't any neighboring cells which the unit could enter.\n\nHowever, the actual move activity is a queued action. Are you maybe immediately calling `actor.Stop()` after `actor.Scatter()`? Then the move to the neighbor cell would be canceled.\n"
