    "body": "What i did was:\n`Utils.Do(BunchaGuys, function(a)\n    if not a.IsDead then\n        a.Scatter()\n    end\nend)`\nI urge you to show me my mistake.\n\nAs a clarification, it only happened once during all of my tests. Unfortunately, Scatter() working properly 99.9999% of the time is not quite good enough, because it requires the application of hacks to make it work in cases when you specifically _need_ those BunchaGuys to clear the area.\n\nMeanwhile, it has been suggested that the canceled move order might be related to #5968. If that is the case, could someone suggest a sensible workaround until this gets addressed?\n"
